Package: ThermalEV
Type: Package
Title: Analyse LeafSpy Logs to Estimate Thermal Parameters of a Nissan Battery
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Thomborson", "Clark",
      email = "c.thomborson@auckland.ac.nz",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Uses nlm() to find best-fit parameters for a simple thermal model
  with three primary parameters.  The effective resistance of the pack is
  the first parameter, in Ohms.  When multiplied by the square of the amperage, 
  this gives the "Joule heating" in Watts.  The other parameters are time 
  constants (in seconds) for the dissipation of the Joule heat, first to the
  outside of the battery modules (where the thermosensors are mounted), and
  then to the ambient air. We also provide some plotting routines.
